{{Infobox award | name = Golden Phoenix Awards | image = | imagesize = | caption = | description = Excellence in film and television by members of the [[China Film Performance Art Academy]] | presenter = [[China Film Performance Art Academy]] | country = [[China]] | year = 1987 | website = }}
'''Golden Phoenix Awards''' ({{zh|t=金鳳凰獎|s=金凤凰奖|p=Jīnfènghuáng Jiăng}}), China's equivalent to the [[Screen Actors Guild Awards]], is a bi-annual accolade given by the [[China Film Performance Art Academy]] to recognize outstanding performances in film. In 1987, the first annual awards ceremony held in [[Guangzhou]].<ref>[http://epaper.qlwb.com.cn/html/2011-06/23/content_147375.htm 中国电影金凤凰奖表彰典礼落户开发区] Qilu Evening Post June 23, 2011</ref>
Because the Society Award is the only regular category that judges the actors' performances, there are multiple winners in the category. Honorary Awards are given to actors aged 60–70, while the Lifetime Achievement Award is given to actors who are over 80 years old. Since 2005, actors from Taiwan and Hong Kong have also eligible for awards.<ref>[http://ent.qq.com/a/20041126/000053.htm 第十届中国电影金凤凰奖定日程 不排斥港台演员] QQ.com November 26, 2004</ref>
The statuette is in a shape of phoenix, designed by artist [[Han Meilin]].<ref>[http://news.artxun.com/diaosu-1243-6212897.shtml 著名美术家韩美林青岛凤凰岛上塑凤凰] Artxun.com March 24, 2008</ref>
==Categories== *Society Award (表演学会奖) *Special Jury Award (评委会特别奖) *New Actors Award (新人奖) *Honorary Award (特别荣誉奖) *Lifetime Achievement Award (终身成就奖)
